---
title: recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs (fulu-polynomial-commitments-sampling)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_assert_len : assert len(cell_indices) == len(cells)
    q_assert_len --> q_assert_count : assert CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB / 2 <= len(cell_indices) <= CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB
    q_assert_count --> q_assert_unique : assert no duplicate cell_indices
    q_assert_unique --> q_assert_sorted : assert cell_indices == sorted(cell_indices)
    q_assert_sorted --> q_assert_bounds : for each cell_index assert < CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB
    q_assert_bounds --> q_assert_cell_len : for each cell assert len == BYTES_PER_CELL
    q_assert_cell_len --> q_convert : cosets_evals = [cell_to_coset_evals(cell) for cell in cells]
    q_convert --> q_recover : polynomial_coeff = recover_polynomialcoeff(cell_indices, cosets_evals)
    q_recover --> q_recompute : result = compute_cells_and_kzg_proofs_polynomialcoeff(polynomial_coeff)
    q_recompute --> [*] : return result

    note right of q_assert_count
        INV: At least CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB / 2 cells required (50% threshold)
        INV: Cell indices must be unique and in ascending order
        INV: All cell indices must be in [0, CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB)
        INV: Recovery uses Reed-Solomon erasure coding with FFT-based reconstruction
    end note
